TY  - JOUR
T1  - Incorporating Workflow Interference in Facility Layout Design: The Quartic Assignment Problem
AU  - Chiang, Wen-Chyuan
AU  - Kouvelis, Panagiotis
AU  - Urban, Timothy L.
Y1  - 2002/04/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.48.4.584.206
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.48.4.584.206
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 584
EP  - 590
VL  - 48
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Although many authors have noted the importance of minimizing workflow interference in facility layout design, traditional layout research tends to focus on minimizing the distance-based transportation cost. This paper formalizes the concept of workflow interference from a facility layout perspective. A model, formulated as a quartic assignment problem, is developed that explicitly considers the interference of workflow. Optimal and heuristic solution methodologies are developed and evaluated.
AB  - Although many authors have noted the importance of minimizing workflow interference in facility layout design, traditional layout research tends to focus on minimizing the distance-based transportation cost. This paper formalizes the concept of workflow interference from a facility layout perspective. A model, formulated as a quartic assignment problem, is developed that explicitly considers the interference of workflow. Optimal and heuristic solution methodologies are developed and evaluated.
